default“Where an infringement of an 
defaultindividual's human rights has occurred, the concern will usually be to bring the infringement to an end and any question of compensation will be of secondary, if any, importance. This is reflected in the fact that, when it is necessary to resort to the cou
defaultrts to uphold and protect human rights
default, the remedies that are most frequently sought are the orders which are the descendants of the historic prerogative orders or declaratory judgmentsdefault. The orders enable the court to order a public body to refrain from or
default to take action, or to quash an offending administrative decision of a public body.”
