defaultAn application for permission carries a relatively high risk of initial failure. Even where a claim is meritorious it is often necessary to persist to an oral hearing or further to obtain permission. 
defaultFor example, while 
defaultWood v Commissioner of Police
default is now
default a leading case on privacy and police records, p
defaultermission
default for judicial review
default was only granted on appeal. 
default 
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultJudicial review claims are “front loaded” in 
defaultthat most of the work from the c
defaultlaimant’s perspective must be done at the stage of brin
defaultg
defaulting the claim. Practitioners therefore have to invest a large amount of time, cost and effort for which they may not get paid. This is increased still further if they have to proceed to an oral hearing or appeal. 
